<div2 type="military" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Military Notices.</head> 
<div3 type="orders" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head rend="smallcaps"><orgName n="Office of the Chief Quartermaster" type="government">Office of Chief Quartermaster</orgName>,<lb /><orgName n="Army of Northern Virginia" type="army">army of Northern Va</orgName>.,</head> <opener> <dateline> <name type="place">Richmond,</name> <date value="07-12" authname="7-12">July 12.</date> </dateline> </opener> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="346" />All Quartermasters, or other persons having in their possession captured Horses or Mules, will at once turn them over to <rs type="role2">Captain</rs> W. S.<hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="Wood,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00198" reg="mostcommon:Wood,nomatch:0" authname="wood"><surname full="yes">Wood</surname></persName>, a. q. m., </hi> at <placeName reg="Bacon Quarter Branch">Bacon Quarter Branch</placeName>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Corley,,James,L.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00199" reg="default:Corley,James,L.,," authname="corley,james,l."><foreName n="James" full="yes">Jas.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">L.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Corley</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> jy <num value="14">14</num>--6t* <rs type="role" reg="Lieutenant-Colonel">Lieut. Col.</rs> and Chief Q. M. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Notice to Commandants of Companies.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="347" /> --Commandants of Companies who desire to have their companies mustered into service, or for pay, will find the office of <persName n="Winder,General,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00200" reg="mostcommon:Winder,nomatch:0" authname="winder"><roleName n="General" full="yes">Gen.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Winder</surname></persName>, during office hours. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Bayly,,Samuel,T.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00201" reg="default:Bayly,Samuel,T.,," authname="bayly,samuel,t."><foreName full="yes">Samuel</foreName> <foreName full="yes">T.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Bayly</surname></persName>,</signed> <rs type="role">Capt.</rs> P. A. C. S., <lb /> jy <num value="14">14</num>--6t* <persName n="Gen,,A.,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00202" reg="default:Gen,A.,A.,," authname="gen,a.,a."><foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Gen</surname></persName>'l and Mustering Officer. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="3" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="348" /> I Am authorized by the <rs>Governor</rs> to raise a regiment of Cavalry, to serve under <persName n="Floyd,Major-General,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00203" reg="mostcommon:Floyd,nomatch:0" authname="floyd"><roleName n="Major-General" full="yes">Major-General</roleName> <surname full="yes">Floyd</surname></persName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="349" />Persons wishing to get up, or assist in getting up, companies for this regiment, can do so by seeing or writing to me at <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Johnson,,J.,E.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00204" reg="default:Johnson,J.,E.,," authname="johnson,j.,e."><foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Johnson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> (Late <rs type="role" reg="Colonel">Colonel</rs> <orgName type="regiment" key="9VACav">9th Va. Cavalry</orgName>,) <lb /> je <num value="27">27</num>--1m* <rs type="role">Col.</rs> Cavalry, <orgName n="Division"><persName n="Floyd,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00205" reg="mostcommon:Floyd,nomatch:0" authname="floyd"><surname full="yes">Floyd</surname></persName>'s Division</orgName>. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="4" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="350" />All men absent from my company will report to me by <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Friday</day></dateStruct> next, or send a surgeon's certificate of their inability to do so, or be treated as deserters. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Burfoot,,Thomas,E.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00206" reg="default:Burfoot,Thomas,E.,," authname="burfoot,thomas,e."><foreName n="Thomas" full="yes">Thos.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Burfoot</surname></persName>.</signed> <lb /> jy <num value="21">21</num>--3t* <rs type="role">Capt.</rs> <orgName type="company" n="Company A">Co. A</orgName>. <num value="2" type="ordinal">2d</num> Reg't <orgName type="mil" key="VAVolunteer">Va. Vols.</orgName> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="5" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="351" />this is to notify the following named persons, members of the <orgName n="Hanover Artillery" type="artillery">Hanover Artillery</orgName> viz: </p> 
