<item><persName><foreName full="yes">Frank</foreName></persName> L <persName n="Maddox,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00231" reg="mostcommon:Maddox,nomatch:0" authname="maddox"><surname full="yes">Maddox</surname></persName>, </item> 
<item><persName n="Terrell,,Joseph,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00232" reg="default:Terrell,Joseph,,," authname="terrell,joseph"><foreName full="yes">Joseph</foreName> <surname full="yes">Terrell</surname></persName>, </item> </list> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="353" /> --who are now absent from the company from various reasons, that they are ordered to return to camp immediately.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="354" />Those who fail to present themselves within the space of <num value="1">one</num> week from date will be advertised as deserters, and a reward of <measure n="30dollars" type="currency">$30</measure> offered for the apprehension and delivery of each of them.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="355" />No certificates of disability or unfitness for service from neighborhood physicians will be received, unless the man is in bed or unable to travel.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="356" />Those who can travel, and yet think themselves unfit for service, will report immediately to <hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="McCaw,Doctor,Janes,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00233" reg="default:McCaw,Janes,,," authname="mccaw,janes"><roleName n="Doctor" full="yes">Dr.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Janes</foreName> <surname full="yes">McCaw</surname></persName>,</hi> <placeName reg="Chimboraze Hospital">Chimboraze Hospital</placeName>, and will there receive an examination and abide by the surgeon's decision.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="357" />The company is now stationed on the <orgName n="York River Railroad" type="railroad">York River Railroad</orgName>, <placeName><distance reg="2miles" full="yes" exact="U">two miles</distance> from <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName></placeName>, and is attached to <orgName n="brigade"><persName n="Colquitt,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00234" reg="mostcommon:Colquitt,nomatch:0" authname="colquitt"><surname full="yes">Colquitt</surname></persName>'s brigade</orgName>. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Nelson,,G.,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00235" reg="default:Nelson,G.,W.,," authname="nelson,g.,w."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Nelson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> <rs type="role2">Captain</rs> <orgName n="Hanover Artillery" type="artillery">Hanover Artillery</orgName>. <lb /> Camp near <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <date value="1862-07-14" authname="1862-07-14">July 14, 1862.</date> jy <num value="13">13</num>--6t* </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="6" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Notice to <placeName reg="North Carolina" key="tgn,7007709" authname="tgn,7007709">North Carolina</placeName> State troops.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="358" /> --All Packages and Boxes sent to Regiments by Express or Freight, can be found at the <rs>N. C. Depot</rs>, No, <address><street n="Main Street 228">228 Main st</street></address>. Also, Boxes containing Clothing, &amp;c., from the <rs>State Quartermaster</rs>, marked to the <rs>Colonels</rs> of Regiments. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Watkins,,Claiborne,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00236" reg="default:Watkins,Claiborne,,," authname="watkins,claiborne"><foreName full="yes">Claiborne</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Watkins</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> jy <num value="15">15</num>--1w* Agent <orgName n="Department of North Carolina" type="department">N. C. Department</orgName>. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="7" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><persName n="Fr,General,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00237" reg="mostcommon:Fr,nomatch:0" authname="fr"><roleName n="General" full="yes">Gen'l</roleName> <surname full="yes">Fr</surname></persName>'t Officer. &amp; D. R. R.</head> <opener> <dateline> <name type="place">Richmond,</name> <date value="1862-07-17" authname="1862-07-17">July 17, 1862.</date> </dateline> </opener> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="359" /> to Merchants and Others of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>.--Having no general collector, this is to notify all parties concerned, that all Freights, both up and down, will be (for the present) required to be paid before delivery in my office, at the <orgName n="Danville Railroad" type="railroad">Danville Railroad</orgName> Depot. </p> <closer> <salute>Very respectably,</salute> <signed><persName n="Sampson,,F.,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00238" reg="default:Sampson,F.,J.,," authname="sampson,f.,j."><foreName full="yes">F.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Sampson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> jy <num value="18">18</num>--10t <persName n="Fr,General,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00239" reg="mostcommon:Fr,nomatch:0" authname="fr"><roleName n="General" full="yes">Gen'l</roleName> <surname full="yes">Fr</surname></persName>'t Ag't R &amp; D. R. R. </closer> </div3> </div2> 
