<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="395" /> On the <dateStruct value="--17" full="yes" authname="---17"><day reg="17" full="yes">17th inst.</day></dateStruct>, by <persName n="Wallace,Reverend,I.,T.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00244" reg="default:Wallace,I.,T.,," authname="wallace,i.,t."><roleName n="Reverend" full="yes">Rev.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">I.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">T.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Wallace</surname></persName>, <persName n="Paulding,Mister,J.,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00245" reg="default:Paulding,J.,H.,," authname="paulding,j.,h."><roleName n="Mister" full="yes">Mr.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Paulding</surname></persName> to <persName n="Ross,Miss,Fannie,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00246" reg="default:Ross,Fannie,,," authname="ross,fannie"><roleName n="Miss" full="yes">Miss</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Fannie</foreName> <surname full="yes">Ross</surname></persName>, all of this city. </p> </div3> 
<div3 type="death" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Died,</head> 
<div4 type="obit" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="396" /> On the <date value="07-21" authname="--07-21">21st July,</date> <persName n="Percival,,Clarence,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00247" reg="default:Percival,Clarence,,," authname="percival,clarence"><foreName full="yes">Clarence</foreName> <surname full="yes">Percival</surname></persName>, infant son of T. B. and <persName n="Hewitt,,Addle,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00248" reg="default:Hewitt,Addle,A.,," authname="hewitt,addle,a."><foreName full="yes">Addle</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Hewitt</surname></persName>. </p> <cit><q direct="unspecified"> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>I bend me o'er thy little form, </l><l>Now stiff in death and cold, </l><l>And think another darling lamb </l><l>Has safely reached the fold.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="397" /></l> </lg> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>I see, by faith, a little crown </l><l>Of gold upon thy brow; </l><l>I hear the rusting of thy wings, </l><l>Thou art an angel now. </l> </lg> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>And shall I mourn thy earthly doom, </l><l>Or wish thee back again; </l><l>A traveler to a certain tomb, </l><l>An heir of certain pain!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="398" /></l> </lg> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>No! rather if I need must weep, </l><l>Let mine be tears of joy; </l><l>That unto me this day is born, </l><l>In Heaven, an angel boy!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="399" /></l> </lg> </q><bibl default="NO" /></cit> 
<p> His funeral will take place this (<dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct>) evening, at the residence of his grandfather, <persName n="Mitchell,,R.,D.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00249" reg="default:Mitchell,R.,D.,," authname="mitchell,r.,d."><foreName full="yes">R.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">D.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Mitchell</surname></persName>, at <time value="4.5oclock">4½ o'clock</time>. The friends and acquaintances of the family are respectfully invited to attend. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="400" /> In this city, <date value="07-21" authname="--07-21">July 21st,</date> of injuries received at the <rs n="Battle of Cross Keys" type="battle">battle of Cross Keys</rs>, <date value="06-08" authname="6-08">June 8th,</date> <persName n="Wright,,Richard,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00250" reg="default:Wright,Richard,W.,," authname="wright,richard,w."><foreName full="yes">Richard</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Wright</surname></persName>, in the <num value="40" type="ordinal">40th</num> year of his age. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="401" /> His funeral will take place this morning, at <time value="10oclock">10 o'clock</time>, from the residence of his aunt, <persName n="Courtney,Mrs.,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00251" reg="mostcommon:Courtney,nomatch:0" authname="courtney"><roleName n="Mrs." full="yes">Mrs.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Courtney</surname></persName>, on <address><street n="Leigh street">Leigh street</street></address>, above <address><street n="Brook Avenue">Brook Avenue</street></address>. The friends of the family, and those of his cousin, <persName n="Steel,Mrs.,Joseph,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00252" reg="default:Steel,Joseph,,," authname="steel,joseph"><roleName n="Mrs." full="yes">Mrs.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Joseph</foreName> <surname full="yes">Steel</surname></persName>, are respectfully invited to attend. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="3" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="402" /> On <dateStruct value="--21" full="yes" authname="---21"><day type="name" full="yes">Monday</day>, <day reg="21" full="yes">21st inst.</day></dateStruct>, at <time value="9:5am">9½ o'clock A. M.</time>, <persName n="Eliza,,Ann,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00253" reg="default:Eliza,Ann,,," authname="eliza,ann"><foreName full="yes">Ann</foreName> <surname full="yes">Eliza</surname></persName>, wife of <persName n="Higgins,,Robert,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00254" reg="default:Higgins,Robert,J.,," authname="higgins,robert,j."><foreName full="yes">Robert</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Higgins</surname></persName>, in the <num value="42" type="ordinal">42d</num> year of her age. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="403" /> The funeral will take place this day, (<dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct>,) from <placeName reg="St. John's Church">St. John's Church</placeName>, at <time value="4pm">4 o'clock P. M.</time> The friends of the family, and of her father, <persName n="Greanor,Mister,William,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00255" reg="default:Greanor,William,,," authname="greanor,william"><roleName n="Mister" full="yes">Mr.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">William</foreName> <surname full="yes">Greanor</surname></persName>, are invited to attend. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="4" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="404" /> On <date>Monday</date>, the <dateStruct value="--21" full="yes" authname="---21"><day reg="21" full="yes">21st instant</day></dateStruct>, at <time value="7:30oclock">half-past 7 o'clock</time> A. M., <persName n="Randolph,,Peyton,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00256" reg="default:Randolph,Peyton,,," authname="randolph,peyton"><foreName full="yes">Peyton</foreName> <surname full="yes">Randolph</surname></persName>, youngest son of M. W. and <persName n="Yarrington,,Sallie,P.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00257" reg="default:Yarrington,Sallie,P.,," authname="yarrington,sallie,p."><foreName full="yes">Sallie</foreName> <foreName full="yes">P.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Yarrington</surname></persName>, aged <measure n="10months" type="date">10 months</measure> and <measure n="14days" type="date">14 days</measure>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="405" /> His funeral will take place from his father's residence on <address><street n="Franklin street">Franklin street</street></address>, between <address><street n="23 Street">23d</street></address> and <address><street n="24 Street">24th</street></address> streets, this day at <time value="5pm">5 o'clock P. M.</time> The friends and acquaintances of the family, and those of his grand parents, <persName n="Yarrington,,James,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00258" reg="default:Yarrington,James,,," authname="yarrington,james"><foreName full="yes">James</foreName> <surname full="yes">Yarrington</surname></persName> and <persName n="Lester,,John,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00259" reg="default:Lester,John,,," authname="lester,john"><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <surname full="yes">Lester</surname></persName>, are respectfully invited to attend without further notice. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="5" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="406" /> On the <dateStruct value="--21" full="yes" authname="---21"><day reg="21" full="yes">21st inst.</day></dateStruct>, at <unclear /><time value=".5oclock">½ o'clock</time>, after a long and severe illness, <persName n="Virginia,,Adia,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00260" reg="default:Virginia,Adia,,," authname="virginia,adia"><foreName full="yes">Adia</foreName> <surname full="yes">Virginia</surname></persName>, youngest daughter of J. B. and E. A. <unclear>Hair</unclear> aged <measure n="9months" type="date">9 months</measure> and <measure n="17days" type="date">17 days</measure>. </p> <cit><q direct="unspecified"> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>Rest, sweets Adia, oh, my love!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="407" /></l><l>Since we are forced to part; </l><l>'Twas that dear <persName><foreName full="yes">Jesus</foreName></persName> from above, </l><l>That took you from our hearts.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="408" /></l> </lg> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>And yet we would not call thee back, </l><l>Our darling Adia, thou art blest, </l><l>We hope to meet thee in that land, </l><l>Where weary spirits sweetly rest.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="409" /></l> </lg> </q><bibl default="NO" /></cit> 
<p> The friends and acquaintances of the family are requested to attend her funeral from the <orgName n="Methodist Church" type="church">Methodist Church</orgName> in <placeName key="tgn,2625188" n="1.000 10" reg="Rocketts, Henrico, Virginia" authname="tgn,2625188">Rocketts</placeName>, <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct> <time>evening</time>, at <time value="4oclock">4 o'clock</time>, without further notice. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="410" /> <placeName reg="Petersburg, Petersburg, Virginia" key="tgn,7014404" authname="tgn,7014404">Petersburg</placeName> papers please copy. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="6" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="411" /> On <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Saturday</day></dateStruct>, <date value="07-19" authname="--07-19">July 19th,</date> Lenora Cabanis, infant daughter of <persName><foreName full="yes">Martha</foreName></persName> D. and <persName n="Sweeney,,Martin,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00261" reg="default:Sweeney,Martin,,," authname="sweeney,martin"><foreName full="yes">Martin</foreName> <surname full="yes">Sweeney</surname></persName>, aged <measure n="14months" type="date">14 months</measure> and <measure n="9days" type="date">9 days</measure>. </p> <cit><q direct="unspecified"> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l><q direct="unspecified">"I take these little lambs,"</q> said he, </l><l>"And lay them on my breast; </l><l>Protection they shall find in me-- </l><l>In me be ever blest." </l> </lg> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>"Their feeble frames my power shall raise, </l><l>And mould with heavenly skill; </l><l>I'll give them tongues to sing my praise, </l><l>And hands to do my will." </l> </lg> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>His words the happy parents hear, </l><l>And shout with joys divine: </l><l>O, Saviour, all we have and are, </l><l>Shall be forever thine.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="412" /></l> </lg> </q><bibl default="NO" /></cit> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="7" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p> In this city, on <date>Sunday</date>, the <dateStruct value="--20" full="yes" authname="---20"><day reg="20" full="yes">20th instant</day></dateStruct>, after a brief illness, <persName><foreName full="yes">Robert</foreName></persName> A., infant son of <persName n="Jas,Lieutenant,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00262" reg="mostcommon:Jas,nomatch:0" authname="jas"><roleName n="Lieutenant" full="yes">Lieut.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Jas</surname></persName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="413" />E. and <persName n="Armour,,Sarah,E.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00263" reg="default:Armour,Sarah,E.,," authname="armour,sarah,e."><foreName full="yes">Sarah</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Armour</surname></persName>, of <persName n="LaGrange,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00264" reg="mostcommon:LaGrange,nomatch:0" authname="lagrange"><surname full="yes">LaGrange</surname></persName>, Missouri, aged <measure n="6years" type="date">6 years</measure> and <measure n="9months" type="date">9 months</measure>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="414" /> Well might it be said of the departed, <q direct="unspecified">"Those whom the <name>Gods</name> love die young."</q> Never again will his merry voice and joyful laugh make glad those who surrounded him in his prairie home of the far <rs>West</rs>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="415" />But we are assured our loss is his gain. </p> <cit><q direct="unspecified"> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>"Farewell, Bobbie dear, farewell; </l><l>Although our hearts now throb with pain, </l><l>We know with <persName><foreName full="yes">Jesus</foreName></persName> thou dost dwell, </l><l>And dare not wish thee back again." J. </l> </lg> </q><bibl default="NO" /></cit> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="8" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="416" /> In <placeName reg="Surry, Virginia, United States" key="tgn,1002931" authname="tgn,1002931">Surry county</placeName>, at the residence of <persName n="Clayton,Mister,Jasper,A.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00265" reg="default:Clayton,Jasper,A.,," authname="clayton,jasper,a."><roleName n="Mister" full="yes">Mr.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Jasper</foreName> <foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Clayton</surname></persName>, on the <date value="07-08" authname="7-08">8th of July,</date> <persName><foreName full="yes">Eugene</foreName></persName>, child of <persName n="Thomas,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00266" reg="mostcommon:Thomas,nomatch:0" authname="thomas"><surname full="yes">Thomas</surname></persName> A, and <persName n="Pollard,,Bettle,J.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00267" reg="default:Pollard,Bettle,J.,," authname="pollard,bettle,j."><foreName full="yes">Bettle</foreName> <foreName full="yes">J.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Pollard</surname></persName>, aged <measure n="11months" type="date">11 months</measure> and <measure n="21days" type="date">21 days</measure>. </p> <cit><q direct="unspecified"> <lg type="stanza" org="uniform" sample="complete"> <l>On earth so lovely and bright, </l><l>Still lovelier in his Saviours sight.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="417" /></l> </lg> </q><bibl default="NO" /></cit> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="9" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p> On the <dateStruct value="--19" full="yes" authname="---19"><day reg="19" full="yes">19th inst.</day></dateStruct>, of wounds received in the battle of the <dateStruct value="--1" full="yes" authname="---01"><day reg="1" full="yes">1st inst.</day></dateStruct>, <persName n="Turner,,William,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00268" reg="default:Turner,William,H.,," authname="turner,william,h."><foreName full="yes">William</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Turner</surname></persName>, <orgName type="regiment" key="Regiment 3">3d Regiment</orgName> <orgName type="mil" key="ALVolunteer">Ala. Volunteers</orgName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="418" /> Sleep quietly, noble <num value="1">one</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="419" />You have won honor imperishable.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="420" />Your country has lost a worthy patriot, and your cause a brave defender. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="421" /> <placeName reg="Montgomery, Montgomery, Alabama" key="tgn,7013928" authname="tgn,7013928">Montgomery, Ala.</placeName>, and <placeName reg="Lowndes, Mississippi, United States" key="tgn,2001129" authname="tgn,2001129">Lowndes county</placeName> papers please copy. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="10" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="422" /> On <date>Saturday</date>, the <dateStruct value="--19" full="yes" authname="---19"><day reg="19" full="yes">19th inst.</day></dateStruct>, <placeName reg="Charlotte, Mecklenburg, North Carolina" key="tgn,7013584" authname="tgn,7013584">Charlotte</placeName>, wife of <persName n="Paul,,Lorenzo,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00269" reg="default:Paul,Lorenzo,,," authname="paul,lorenzo"><foreName full="yes">Lorenzo</foreName> <surname full="yes">Paul</surname></persName>, in the <num value="50" type="ordinal">50th</num> year of her age. She leaves a husband and <num value="7">seven</num> children to mourn their loss. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="11" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head>Obituaries.</head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="423" /><persName n="Gay,,Charles,Wyndham,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00270" reg="default:Gay,Charles,Wyndham,," authname="gay,charles,wyndham"><foreName full="yes">Charles</foreName> <foreName full="yes">Wyndham</foreName> <surname full="yes">Gay</surname></persName>.--On <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct>, the <date value="07-01" authname="7-01">first day of July,</date> <hi rend="smallcaps"><persName n="Gay,,Charles,Wyndham,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00271" reg="default:Gay,Charles,Wyndham,," authname="gay,charles,wyndham"><foreName full="yes">Charles</foreName> <foreName full="yes">Wyndham</foreName> <surname full="yes">Gay</surname></persName>,</hi> in his <num value="21" type="ordinal">21st</num> year, eldest son of <persName><foreName full="yes">Charles</foreName></persName> S. and <persName n="Gay,,Margaret,L.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00272" reg="default:Gay,Margaret,L.,," authname="gay,margaret,l."><foreName full="yes">Margaret</foreName> <foreName full="yes">L.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Gay</surname></persName>, of <placeName reg="Augusta, Virginia, United States" key="tgn,2002142" authname="tgn,2002142">Augusta county, Va.</placeName>, and a member of the <orgName n="Danville Artillery" type="artillery">Danville Artillery</orgName>, was killed on the battlefield below <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="424" />His devoted comrades in arms, among whom was <num value="1">one</num> of his brothers, wrapped him in his blanket and carefully laid him in an adjacent church-yard, thence to be removed by warm hearted and affectionate friends to the city of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, and now reposes under the sweet shades of <placeName key="tgn,2008520" n="1.000 1" reg="hollywood, clark, arkansas" authname="tgn,2008520">Hollywood</placeName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="425" />No rude or unfriendly hand touched him after the fatal missile had done its work.--He was tenderly cared for by those who knew him; was mourned over by sympathising hearts, as the solemn words were spoken by <name n="God" type="God">God's</name> minister.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="426" />He was borne to his quiet resting place by loving hands, and his grave was watered by tears of affection and covered with flowers fresh and beautiful as were the hopes of his young heart a few hours before!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="427" />And yet, father, mother, brothers and sisters, were far away!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="428" /><name n="God" type="God">God</name> reward those who thus cared for the young soldier in his death! </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="429" /> Attached to the blanket containing his body was found a slip of paper, on which were written his name, place of residence, and some particulars of his death, concluding with these words: <q direct="unspecified">"<hi rend="italics">He died nobly in defence of Southern freedom.</hi>"</q> </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="430" /> And so the young hero sleeps well.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="431" /><hi rend="italics">His</hi> work is done, <hi rend="italics">his</hi> duties over, and his bright spirit has winged its upward flight to <name n="God" type="God">God</name> who gave it! </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="432" /> Among the many who have fallen in defence of our sacred cause, no purer, truer, or more noble martyr, has yielded up his life.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="433" />None but those who knew his inner nature could fully appreciate his virtues.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="434" />A student by habit and choice, a ripe scholar for his age, matured in thought and judgment beyond his years, truthful to a proverb, following duties in its thorniest paths with cheerful alacrity, pure and modest as a girl, never known to utter a profane word, a son who never gave a pang of grief to a parent's heart, and, above all, as we feel assured, a Christian warrior, he fell, with his Bible near his heart, in the front of battle, just as the true hero prays to die. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="435" /> Soon after the war commenced he consecrated himself to his country's service, never pausing to inquire who will go or who will stay, but, taking his younger brother by the hand, he stepped forth to fight for country and for freedom.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="436" />Once only did his mother, knowing how delicate his health had been, venture to suggest to him that some other situation could be procured for him, equally useful, and perhaps less exposed, than that of a soldier.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="437" />He burst into manly tears, saying, <q direct="unspecified">"Mother, I did not expect that of you!"</q> </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="438" /> Ever after, that mother's prayers followed him like angels, and bore him through the trials and perils of war; and in the final moment, we doubt not, with a wall of human agony heard in the spirit land, gave him over to angels' hands, to be borne by them to his Saviour's side.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="439" />And still let us who remain, though sorrowing and in tears, with cheerful faith that <q direct="unspecified">"all is full of blessings,"</q> with undying love of liberty and unfaltering trust in <name n="God" type="God">God</name>, pray for peace and fight to win it!

<milestone unit="sentence" n="440" />and the dawning smile of our favoring <name n="God" type="God">God</name> shall grow brighter into the perfect day of <hi rend="smallcaps">National Independence.</hi> </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="441" /> S. </p> </div4> 
<div4 type="obit" n="12" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<p> Died, on <date>Sunday</date>, the <dateStruct value="--13" full="yes" authname="---13"><day reg="13" full="yes">13th inst.</day></dateStruct>, in <placeName reg="Orange, Virginia, United States" key="tgn,2002177" authname="tgn,2002177">Orange county, Va.</placeName>, during the raid into that county by <persName n="Pope,General,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00273" reg="mostcommon:Pope,nomatch:0" authname="pope"><roleName n="General" full="yes">General</roleName> <surname full="yes">Pope</surname></persName>'s Yankee hirelings, of wounds received the preceding day, <persName n="Maxwell,Mister,William,B.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00274" reg="default:Maxwell,William,B.,," authname="maxwell,william,b."><roleName n="Mister" full="yes">Mr.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">William</foreName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Maxwell</surname></persName>, late of <placeName reg="Washington, District of Columbia" key="tgn,7013962" authname="tgn,7013962">Washington, D. C.</placeName>, aged about <measure n="33years" type="date">33 years</measure>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="442" /> <persName n="Maxwell,Mister,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00275" reg="nearbymention:Maxwell,William,B.,," authname="maxwell,william,b."><roleName n="Mister" full="yes">Mr.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Maxwell</surname></persName>, while sleeping with his face to his couch, was shot in the spine and hand by a denizen of <placeName reg="Washington, District of Columbia, United States" key="tgn,7013962" authname="tgn,7013962">Washington</placeName>, who recognized the unfortunate exile.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="443" />He left his home, wife, children and aged mother, in <date value="1861-04" authname="1861-04">April, 1861,</date> urged on by an unfaltering principle of resistance to the vandal <rs>North</rs>, and love for freedom and the holy cause of the oppressed <rs>South</rs>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="444" />He was elected 2d <rs type="role2">Lieutenant</rs> of <orgName type="company" n="Company E">Company E</orgName>, <orgName type="regiment" key="1VARegiment">1st Va. regiment</orgName>, (Company <q direct="unspecified"> "A,"</q> <orgName n="Washington volunteers" type="volunteers">Washington volunteers</orgName>,) and served the <orgName n="Confederate Government" type="org">Confederate Government</orgName> faithfully, honorably and bravely on the bloody fields of <placeName reg="Bull Run, Prince William, Virginia" key="tgn,7013988" authname="tgn,7013988">Bull Run</placeName> and <placeName key="tgn,2112877" n="1.000 541" reg="manassas, manassas, virginia" authname="tgn,2112877">Manassas</placeName>, and was on duty with his company up to the expiration of its term of service, (<date value="1862-05-12" authname="1862-05-12">May 12th, 1862, </date>) when it was disbanded. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="445" /> <persName n="Maxwell,Mister,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00276" reg="nearbymention:Maxwell,William,B.,," authname="maxwell,william,b."><roleName n="Mister" full="yes">Mr.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Maxwell</surname></persName> was noted among his many friends for his untiring energy, high principle, unwavering courage, and peculiarly for his amiable and affectionate disposition.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="446" />Hard indeed was his fate, to have met his doom at the hands of an assassin, in a strange land, away from friends, home, wife, children and mother.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="447" />Peace to his ashes. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="448" /> [*] R. C. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="449" /> That brave spirit, who deeply feels the wrongs inflicted upon his country and his people by a despot; who resists, step by step, the tread of the invader; who faiters not in his determination to repel him in his march; who sacrifices health, property, comforts, pleasures and interest, in driving him from his soil; who endangers his life in defence of rights dear only to freemen; who, in the extremity of seal, calmly bares his breast to the storm of leaden hall, and yields freely his blood in defence and in honor of our fair country and its holy cause; who, without promise or hope of earthly reward — save that, the greatest of all, a consciousness of having discharged a sacred duty — still battling, falls a martyr to a high and glorious cause — that man, that soldier, is the true patriot.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="450" />Such an <num value="1">one</num> was <persName n="Hart,Private,John,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00277" reg="default:Hart,John,,," authname="hart,john"><roleName n="Private" full="yes">Private</roleName> <foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <surname full="yes">Hart</surname></persName>, of <placeName reg="Alexandria, Alexandria, Virginia" key="tgn,7013269" authname="tgn,7013269">Alexandria, Virginia</placeName>, <orgName type="company" n="Company A">Company A</orgName>, <orgName type="regiment" n="Reg. 17">17th Reg.</orgName> <orgName type="mil" key="VAVolunteer">Va. Volunteers</orgName>, who fall mortally wounded in front of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, in the <rs n="Battle of Monday" type="battle">battle of Monday</rs>, <date value="06-30" authname="--06-30">30th June,</date> whist gallantly </p> <milestone unit="column" n="3" /> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="451" /> engaged in repulsing a flank movement of the enemy, directed against the <orgName n="Left Wing" type="wing">left wing</orgName> of his regiment.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="452" />Being wounded in the right hip severely, he sank down and leaned against a tree for support; during which time, the position of his regiment being changed, he was approached from behind by <num value="2">two</num> <placeName reg="Yankees">Yankees</placeName>, <num value="1">one</num> of whom deliberately raised his rifle and sent a ball crashing through his body, just below the right shoulder; after which they rifled his pockets of his watch and other articles.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="453" />When the ground was retaken by our troops, <persName n="Hart,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00278" reg="nearbymention:Hart,John,,," authname="hart,john"><surname full="yes">Hart</surname></persName> was found still living.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="454" />He was carried to <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, attended by skillful surgeons, nursed by a devoted sister and many friends; but the last murderous wound was too much for his already exhausted system, for on the morning of the <date value="07-13" authname="--07-13">13th July,</date> at <time value="1:20oclock">20 minutes past 1 o'clock</time>, after bearing his wounds like a true hero, he yielded up his generous and noble life, in the full hope of a blissful immortality, in the <num value="22" type="ordinal">22d</num> year of his age. [*] J. R. S. </p> </div4> </div3> </div2> 
<div2 type="announcements" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head /> 
<div3 type="orders" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><hi rend="smallcaps">Camp of <orgName type="regiment" key="3VACav">3d Virginia Cavalry</orgName>, white house,</hi> <date value="1862-07-12" authname="1862-07-12">July 12, 1862,</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="455" />Tribute of Respect.--At a called meeting of the <rs type="place">Charles City</rs> Troop, for the purpose of giving expression to their feelings regarding the loss of their late <rs type="role" reg="Captain">Captain</rs>, <persName n="Harrison,,B.,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00279" reg="default:Harrison,B.,H.,," authname="harrison,b.,h."><foreName full="yes">B.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Harrison</surname></persName>, <persName n="Guy,Lieutenant,F.,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00280" reg="default:Guy,F.,,," authname="guy,f."><roleName n="Lieutenant" full="yes">Lieut.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">F.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Guy</surname></persName> was called to the <name>Chair</name> and <persName n="Lamb,Sergeant,John,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00281" reg="default:Lamb,John,,," authname="lamb,john"><roleName n="Sergeant" full="yes">Sergt.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <surname full="yes">Lamb</surname></persName> appointed <rs type="role2">Secretary</rs>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="456" /> On motion, the following committee was appointed to draft resolutions, viz: <persName n="Carter,Lieutenant,Hill,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00282" reg="default:Carter,Hill,,," authname="carter,hill"><roleName n="Lieutenant" full="yes">Lieut.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">Hill</foreName> <surname full="yes">Carter</surname></persName>, <persName n="McClelland,,John,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00283" reg="default:McClelland,John,,," authname="mcclelland,john"><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <surname full="yes">McClelland</surname></persName>, <persName n="Pollard,,Thomas,F.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00284" reg="default:Pollard,Thomas,F.,," authname="pollard,thomas,f."><foreName full="yes">Thomas</foreName> <foreName full="yes">F.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Pollard</surname></persName>, <persName n="Clarke,,A.,T.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00285" reg="default:Clarke,A.,T.,," authname="clarke,a.,t."><foreName full="yes">A.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">T.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Clarke</surname></persName>, <persName n="Bowrey,,G.,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00286" reg="default:Bowrey,G.,W.,," authname="bowrey,g.,w."><foreName full="yes">G.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Bowrey</surname></persName>, and <persName n="Waddill,,R.,E.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00287" reg="default:Waddill,R.,E.,," authname="waddill,r.,e."><foreName full="yes">R.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">E.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Waddill</surname></persName>. </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="457" /> The committee then reported the following preamble and resolutions, which were unanimously adopted by the meeting: </p> <cit><q direct="unspecified"> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="458" /> Whereas, it hath pleased Almighty <name n="God" type="God">God</name>, in his inscrutable wisdom, to take from us our beloved <rs type="role2">Captain</rs>, friend, and brother, (for he was both friend and brother to us all,) and inasmuch as he fell so nobly in endeavoring to rally and lead again to the charge a regiment whose field officers had all fallen in the glorious cause of driving the invader from the hearths and firesides of our loved Capital, be it resolved-- </p> 
<list type="ordered"> 
<head /> 
<item n="1"> <num value="1" type="ordinal">1st</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="459" />That we, the members of the <rs type="place">Charles City</rs> Troop, being filled with the most sincere, unfeigned and heartfelt sorrow for the loss we, as a company and individuals, have sustained, adopt the means at this our earliest opportunity, of publicly expressing our feelings and sentiments on the occasion, that our country and State may know that we, in some measure at least, appreciate the high character and eminent worth of the noble heart that glowed with brightest lustre in the bosom of our late <hi rend="italics">gallant</hi> commander.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="460" /></item> 
<item n="2"> <num value="2" type="ordinal">2d</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="461" />We feel that our country's loss has been great, very great, in the untimely death of <persName n="Harrison,Captain,B.,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00288" reg="default:Harrison,B.,H.,," authname="harrison,b.,h."><roleName n="Captain" full="yes">Captain</roleName> <foreName full="yes">B.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Harrison</surname></persName>; for his many qualifications as a military leader indicated for him a path of high honor and usefulness.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="462" /></item> 
<item n="3"> <num value="3" type="ordinal">3d</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="463" />That the amiable qualities and public spirit, so pure and unselfish, that characterized the deceased, is an example worthy of imitation by us all, and should incite us to nobler deeds and greater usefulness in the cause now claiming our devotion and energies.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="464" /></item> 
<item n="4"> <num value="4" type="ordinal">4th</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="465" />That for the companion of his bosom, the relatives of his blood, we would pause and offer to mingle our tears and sympathies; for if it has proved so hard for us to give him up, who have known and loved him but a few short months, how bitter, indeed, must be their cup who have even cherished him in the dearest relations of life.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="466" /></item> 
<item n="5"> <num value="5" type="ordinal">5th</num>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="467" />That these proceedings be published in the <orgName n="Richmond Enquirer" type="newspaper">Richmond Enquirer</orgName> and Dispatch and a copy also be forwarded to the family of the deceased.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="468" /></item> </list> </q></cit> <closer> <signed><persName n="Guy,Lieutenant,F.,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00289" reg="default:Guy,F.,,," authname="guy,f."><roleName n="Lieutenant" full="yes">Lieut.</roleName> <foreName full="yes">F.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Guy</surname></persName>,</signed> <rs type="role2">President</rs>. <lb /> <signed>Serg't <persName n="Lamb,,John,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00290" reg="default:Lamb,John,,," authname="lamb,john"><foreName full="yes">John</foreName> <surname full="yes">Lamb</surname></persName>,</signed> <rs type="role2">Secretary</rs>. </closer> </div3> </div2> 
